  "prompt": "What are the symptoms of a bad speed sensor?",
  "response": "A faulty speed sensor can cause a variety of symptoms in your vehicle, as it plays a crucial role in monitoring and transmitting information about your vehicle's speed to the engine control unit (ECU) and other systems. Here are some common symptoms of a bad speed sensor:\n\n### 1. **Erratic Speedometer Readings**\n   - The speedometer may display incorrect speeds, jump erratically, or stop working entirely.\n\n### 2. **Check Engine Light**\n   - A malfunctioning speed sensor can trigger the check engine light (CEL) to illuminate.\n\n### 3. **Transmission Shifting Problems**\n   - Automatic transmissions may experience delayed, harsh, or improper shifting due to incorrect speed data.\n\n### 4. **Cruise Control Failure**\n   - Cruise control may not engage or maintain speed properly if the speed sensor is faulty.\n\n### 5. **ABS Warning Light**\n   - If the speed sensor is linked to the anti-lock braking system (ABS), the ABS warning light may come on.\n\n### 6. **Loss of Power Assistance**\n   - In some vehicles, the power steering or other systems may lose assistance if the speed sensor fails.\n\n### 7. **Poor Fuel Efficiency**\n   - Incorrect speed data can lead to improper fuel mixture and reduced fuel efficiency.\n\n### 8. **Inability to Start**\n   - In some cases, the vehicle may not start if the speed sensor is completely inadequate.\n\n### 9. **ABS or Traction Control Issues**\n   - ABS or traction control systems may malfunction, leading to reduced braking or stability performance.\n\n### 10. **Odometer Miscalculations**\n   - The odometer may stop working or record incorrect mileage due to a faulty speed sensor.\n\nIf you notice any of these symptoms, it's advisable to have your vehicle inspected by a professional mechanic to diagnose and replace the faulty speed sensor if necessary.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
